    @InheritOnly
public interface AbstractThrowingOperatorN<T,H extends AbstractThrowingFunctionN.Handler<T>>
extends AbstractThrowingFunctionN<T,H>
    Represents an operation that accepts n operands and produces a result of the same type as its operands or throws a throwable. All operators are derived from this n-arity specialization. This is a specialization of AbstractThrowingFunctionN where the operands and result are of the same type. This is the throwing variation of OperatorN.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    See Also:
    AbstractThrowingFunctionN, OperatorN
    API Note:
    This is an abstract operator and should not be used directly. It should instead be called by one of its subtypes.
